"n.同情，怜悯 同根词：dispassiona te(a. 心平气和的)；impass ive(a. 冷漠的)反义词：indifferenc e(n. 不关心的) n. 同情怜悯(对别人的痛苦有深入了解, 并且希望他解脱出来) 【例】Her heart was filled with compassion 她充满了怜悯心. 【记】com共同, passion(n 感情)－引起共同感情－同情 【参】dispassionate(adj 心平气和的); impassive(adj 冷淡的)compassionate(adj 有同情心的 = sympathetic) 【反】indifference(n 不关心) 【记】com + passion 同样感情 compassion (n.)  mid-14c., from Old French compassion ""sympathy, pity"" (12c.), from Late Latin compassionem (nominative compassio) ""sympathy,"" noun of state from past participle stem of compati ""to feel pity,"" from com- ""together"" (see com-) + pati ""to suffer"" (see passion). Latin compassio is an ecclesiastical loan-translation of Greek sympatheia (see sympathy). An Old English loan-translation of compassion was efenðrowung."
